From: Lumi Upgrade v1 (orbit-reticle, larger+faster scan-wait mascot)
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] LumiMascot.tsx — orbit math + profile tune + bubble-style split

Three coordinated changes inside the orchestrator:

  1. PROFILES.scanning and PROFILES['looking-up'] get non-zero orbit values
     (radius 90, 28 RPM) so 'orbit-reticle' has work to do during evaluation.
     Trail rate tightens 80ms → 50ms for denser sparkle. scaleBase 0.95 → 1.00
     so Lumi reads at full size during the wait.

  2. New orbit shared-value + animation effect, gated on movement='orbit-reticle'
     AND reduceMotion=false AND non-zero profile orbit values. Linear loop
     around 2π over (60_000 / orbitSpeedRpm) ms.

  3. Anchor resolution gets an early branch for orbit-reticle: uses freePosition
     as the orbit center. bodyAnimStyle composes orbit translate FIRST, then bob,
     then scale. Speech bubble splits off into bubbleAnimStyle (scale only) so
     the bubble stays put while Lumi spins around it.

Reduce Motion: the existing useReducedMotion gate kills the orbit effect, so
Lumi falls back to a static anchor at the reticle center. Honored automatically.

